text: Eric Saade (born 29 October 1990 in Helsingborg, Sweden) is a Swedish- Palestinian singer. He spent two years with as boy band called What's Up!. He left the band in February 2009 to for a solo career. He won the Swedish Melodifestivalen 2011 with the song "Popular". He represented Sweden at the Eurovision Song Contest 2011 in Germany, placing third in the final.
